 PHAKANE -Students attended in hopes of finding out more about what their future careers have in store for them. The Careers Day, hosted by the Rotary Club of White River, did not disappoint and offered stalls on various industries ranging from a career in the South African National Defence Force to chefs, engineers and musicians. ALSO READ: N11 head-on collision claims nine lives It also included workshops on how to put together your CV and how to do an interview. This day was the brainchild of Rotary’s head of youth services, Judy Pott who started it as part of the Interact Club at Fundinjobo. This year was her fifth year hosting the event, while it was the first time that Rotary had gotten involved.  